HEADWORD: Neurokeratin
<hw>Neu`ro*ker"a*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Neuro-</ets> + <ets>keratin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance, resembling keratin, present in nerve
tissue, as in the sheath of the axis cylinder of medullated nerve
fibers. Like keratin it resists the action of most chemical agents, and
by decomposition with sulphuric acid yields leucin and tyrosin.</def><--
myelin ?? -->⟦br⟧
